t with the camshaft drive chain.","Check that the wedges are between the camshaft sprockets and the crankcase.","Check the alignment marks on the front end of the camshaft journals are pointing inwards. ","Camshaft alignment marks","Exhaust camshaft","Inlet camshaft","Check that ","service tool T3880501"," is through the hole in the crankcase.","T3880501 - Crankshaft Locking Pin","Alignment mark","The plunger of the camshaft drive chain tensioner is under spring tension. Always wear hand, eye and facial protection when removing the tensioner as unprotected areas of the body can be injured if the spring tension is released in an unexpected or uncontrolled way.","If installing a new hydraulic tensioner, do not release the plunger before fitting.","If installing the original hydraulic tensioner, the engine oil must be drained out of the tensioner to enable the plunger to be set onto the first tooth of the ratchet.","Hold the resister ring ends together and pull out the plunger.","Resister ring ends","Plunger","Remove the spring.","Spring","While holding the resister ring in place, drain the engine oil into a suitable container.","Make sure the resister ring is correctly located as shown below.","Resister ring","Refit the spring.","Support the tensioner in a soft jawed vice.","Hold the resister ends together, close the vice allowing the plunger to be pushed through the resister ring until the snap ring aligns with the snap ring groove.","Resister ring","Plunger","Snap ring groove","Snap ring","When the snap ring aligns with the snap ring groove, release the vice and move one end of the snap ring into the groove. Slowly release the plunger to make sure it is held in place.","Snap ring groove","Snap ring","Fit two new O-rings to the camshaft drive chain tensioner body.","Fit the tensioner to the cylinder head as noted for removal. Using ","service tool T3880649",", tighten the tensioner to ","16 Nm",".","Remove the two wedges that are between the camshaft sprockets and the crankcase.","Remove ","service tool T3880501",".","T3880501 - Crankshaft Locking Pin","Alignment mark","To release the plunger from the snap ring holding the hydraulic tensioner, rotate the crankshaft anticlockwise until the plunger is released.","Continue to rotate the crankshaft anticlockwise to complete two revolutions and the two gear teeth with an alignment marks are visible and central in the hole for the crankshaft locking pin.","Crankshaft primary gear","Alignment marks","Check that there is tension in the camshaft drive chain and the slot at the camshafts end are correctly aligned.","Camshaft timing slots","Check that the tensioner plunger is correctly located in the middle of the camshaft drive chain tensioner blade when viewed from above.","Rotate the engine through 4 full revolutions, and reset number 1 cylinder to TDC. Make sure that the two gear teeth with an alignment marks are visible in the hole for the crankshaft locking pin.","Fit ","service tool T3880501"," through the hole in the crankcase.","T3880501 - Crankshaft Locking Pin","Alignment mark","Check the alignment marks on the front end of the camshaft journals are pointing inwards. ","Camshaft alignment marks","Exhaust camshaft","Inlet camshaft","Reheck that there is tension in the camshaft drive chain and the slot at the camshafts end are correctly aligned.","Camshft timing slots","Recheck the tensioner plunger location against the camshaft drive chain tensioner blade.","Remove ","service tool T3880501",".","T3880501 - Crankshaft Locking Pin","Alignment mark","Fit the crankshaft locking pin plug and tighten to ","33 Nm",".","Locking pin plug","After fitting to the engine, the hydraulic tensioner will be empty of engine oil. After starting the engine, the camshaft drive chain and tensioner blade will be noisy until full pressure is felt at the tensioner plunger. This could take up to 5 seconds.","Perform the following operations:","Plenum - Installation (All Markets Except US)"," or ","Plenum - Installation (US Markets Only)","Clutch Cover - Installation","Fuel Tank - Installation","Battery - Installation","Seat - Installation"],"viewCount":0,"infoType":"InfoType08","createdAt":"2024-06-20T10:52:02.869Z","updatedAt":"2024-06-20T10:52:02.869Z","__v":0}